article.headline: Penn St. 61, Indiana 58
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. -- Talor Battle scored 16 points and Penn State overcame another subpar performance at the foul line to defeat Indiana 61-58 on Saturday. Jamelle Cornley added 10 points for the Nittany Lions (20-9, 9-7 Big Ten), who reached the 20-win plateau for the first time since 2000-01 -- the last time they made the NCAA tournament. Devan Dumes had 16 for Indiana (6-22, 1-15), which lost its sixth straight. The Hoosiers' 22 losses on the season extended a school record. Verdell Jones III also scored 16 for Indiana, which led 57-53 with 5:26 left before Battle and Cornley sparked the Nittany Lions down the stretch. Battle saved a possession by scrambling for a ball headed out of bounds, then later dished off to Cornley for a dunk that gave Penn State the lead for good with 56 seconds left. Penn State was 7-of-17 on the day from the foul line.
